# User Experience (UX/UI) Interview Q&A Generator

Generate 25-30 interview Q&A pairs for senior/lead/principal UX roles demonstrating design thinking to execution.

## Scope

**Target Roles**: Senior UX designers (5+ years), lead designers, design principals, product designers  
**Context**: Digital products (web/mobile/SaaS), cross-platform design, user-centered methodology  
**Prerequisites**: Design principles, usability heuristics, WCAG accessibility standards  
**Success Criteria**: 19/19 validation checks PASS (see §6)

---

# Requirements

## Questions: Structure & Coverage

| Aspect | Specification |
|--------|---------------|
| **Count** | 25-30 total across 6 dimensions (4-6 per dimension) |
| **Difficulty** | 20% Foundational / 40% Intermediate / 40% Advanced (±5%) |
| **Type** | ≥70% judgment-based ("How/When/Compare..."); <30% recall |
| **Length** | 150-300 words (excluding artifacts) |
| **Flow** | Pattern → rationale → artifacts → trade-offs → metrics |
| **Citations** | ≥1 each (≥2 for advanced questions) |
| **Per Dimension** | 1 diagram + 1 design spec + 1 comparison table + 1 metric formula |

## Dimensions (MECE Coverage)

1. **Research & Testing**: User research, usability testing, analytics, A/B testing, validation methods
2. **Information Architecture**: Navigation, taxonomies, mental models, card sorting, sitemaps
3. **Visual Design & UI**: Layout, typography, color theory, design tokens, grids, visual hierarchy
4. **Interaction Design**: User flows, states, feedback, microinteractions, modal dialogs, progressive disclosure
5. **Accessibility & Inclusion**: WCAG compliance, ARIA, screen readers, inclusive design, i18n
6. **Design Systems**: Component libraries, atomic design, governance, versioning, scalability

## Content Quality Standards

**Traceability**: User Needs → Constraints → Pattern → Design → Metrics  
**Quantified**: ✅ "+35% task completion, -25% engagement" ❌ "Better UX"  
**Contextual**: Specify Team size (solo/<5/>20), Users (<1K/1K-100K/>1M), Platforms (1/2-3/>3), Maturity (MVP/growth/enterprise)  
**Balanced**: ≥2 alternatives + table; explicit assumptions/limitations; tag `[Best Practice]`/`[Context-dependent]`/`[Emerging]`  
**Precise**: Define terms inline; consistent terminology; concrete metrics ("<3 clicks"/"8-12pt", not "easy"/"readable"); avoid jargon

## Artifacts

**Diagram-Design-Metric Mapping**:

| Dimension | Diagram | Design Example | Metric Formula |
|-----------|---------|----------------|----------------|
| Research & Testing | Journey map/Research plan | User interview script | `SUS Score = (Σ scores - 5) × 2.5` |
| Information Architecture | Sitemap/Flow diagram | Navigation structure | `Findability = Found in ≤3 clicks / Total × 100%` |
| Visual Design & UI | Wireframe/Mockup | Component spec (spacing, tokens) | `Contrast Ratio = (L1 + 0.05) / (L2 + 0.05)` |
| Interaction Design | User flow/State diagram | Interaction patterns | `Task Success = Completed / Attempted × 100%` |
| Accessibility | ARIA tree/Keyboard flow | WCAG checklist | `WCAG Compliance = Passed / Total Criteria × 100%` |
| Design Systems | Component library/Token hierarchy | Design token schema | `Adoption = Teams Using / Total Teams × 100%` |

**Format**: Diagrams (Mermaid <120 nodes, type matches dimension); Design specs (Figma/Sketch patterns, annotated, production-ready with states); Tables (quantitative, "Use When" column); Metrics (formula + variables + target)

**Common Patterns**: Progressive Disclosure, Card Sorting, F-Pattern, Z-Pattern, Modal Dialogs, Stepper Forms, Infinite Scroll, Skeleton Loading, Toast Notifications, Atomic Design, Design Tokens, Component Variants

## References

| Component | Min | Requirements |
|-----------|-----|--------------|
| **Glossary** | ≥10 | Terms with relationships (e.g., "Progressive Disclosure: revealing info incrementally. Related: Cognitive Load") |
| **Tools** | ≥5 | URL (valid), update ≤18mo, pricing, adoption metrics |
| **Literature** | ≥6 | Authoritative books (Norman, Krug, Cooper, Gothelf, Knapp, Nielsen) |
| **Citations** | ≥12 | APA 7th, 60% [EN] / 30% [ZH] / 10% other (±10%) |

**Quality**: Recency (≥50% last 3yr, ≥70% digital/web); Diversity (≥3 types, <25% single source); Credibility (research-backed, authoritative); 100% valid links

